  "body": "I am a NixOS user and the binary that hardhat auto-downloads does not work on my system (I'm not actually sure why, dynamic deps all seem to be there but the compiler fails to run with 'ENOENT' so I'm guessing some dependency somewhere is missing)\r\n\r\nI would like to be able to explicitly set a compiler path in the config file.\r\n\r\nFor now, I've hacked a solution via a symlink, but an official solution to this would be ideal.\r\n\r\nMy fix for now:\r\n`ln -s $(which solc) $HOME/.cache/hardhat-nodejs/compilers-v2/linux-amd64/solc-linux-amd64-v0.8.17+commit.8df45f5f`\r\n\r\nObviously this is not ideal because I'm going to have to constantly update this command everytime hardhat pulls an updated solc version.",
